ach of the countries, showing how, after the crisis, it is accelerating the reconfiguration of institutions and practices that are central to the lives of the young. This book is essential reading for students of youth studies, sociology and policy, seeking a greater understanding of international public and social policy in relation to the youth question.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831111964350 cprintz978144731576640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447316961423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447316961/original  a978-3-11-119643-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles